# decimo CLI surface (decoded from DecimoArgs
# struct + post-spec config at main.mojo:34-141):
#   <expr>                       math expression (positional, optional)
#   -F PATH / --file PATH        evaluate expressions from file
#   -P N / --precision N         significant digits (1..1_000_000_000; default 50)
#   -R MODE / --rounding-mode MODE
#                                rounding: half-even|half-up|half-down|up|down|ceiling|floor
#   --delimiter CHAR             digit-group separator (e.g. '_' for 1_234.567_89)
#   -S / --scientific            scientific notation (mutex with -E)
#   -E / --engineering           engineering notation (mutex with -S)
#   --pad                        pad trailing zeros to precision
#   -A / --about                 display version/author/license
#   --info                       alias for --about
#   -h / --help                  argmojo auto-injected
#
# decimo is an arbitrary-precision CLI calculator
# powered by the Decimo Mojo library (BigDecimal).
# Evaluates mathematical expressions with
# user-specified precision (up to 1 billion
# significant digits), supports scientific/
# engineering notation, custom rounding modes,
# and digit-group delimiters.  Authored by Yuhao
# Zhu (forfudan).  23 GH stars.  Sister tools:
# bc (Unix arbitrary-precision calculator, in
# corpus), dc (RPN calculator), python (with
# `decimal` module), GNU Octave (with arbitrary-
# precision via mpfr).
